</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-42_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) USA</strong> - guidelines require employers to train their employees in their jobs' health and safety aspects, influencing similar regulations worldwide.

































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) EU</strong> - This regulation impacts how data protection training is conducted, emphasising the necessity of training all personnel in proper data handling and privacy procedures.











































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 UK</strong> - Mandates that employers provide necessary information, instruction, training, and supervision to ensure employee health and safety as far as is practicable.












































